The paper is about deep steganalysis in computer vision, which involves detecting hidden information in images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep learning and convolutional neural networks, which are common in the sub-categories cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses improving the efficiency of the CNN model, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves detecting weak information in low signal-to-noise cases, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
